      "content": "but it's not just about the money, you don't get it. i was supposed to be the one providing, the one they could rely on. instead i'm just a massive weight around their necks now. i look at my wife and my kids and all i see is the life i'm about to ruin because i was too arrogant to admit i was failing. it feels like the only honest thing left to do is just... stop being a burden. everything feels so heavy and permanent.",
